'''Timothy John "Tim" Armstrong''' (born 26 September 1990) is an Australian [[cricket]]er currently contracted to the [[Perth Scorchers]] in the [[Big Bash League]], having previously played at Australian domestic level with [[New South Wales cricket team|New South Wales]], the [[Sydney Thunder]], and [[Western Australia cricket team|Western Australia]]. From [[Dubbo]], [[New South Wales]], Armstrong was from a strong cricketing family,<ref name="scorchers"/> representing New South Wales at under-17 and under-19 level,<ref>[http://cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Players/255/255691/Miscellaneous_Matches.html Miscellaneous Matches played by Tim Armstrong (65)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> and going on to represent the [[Australia Under-19 cricket team|Australian under-19 cricket team]] at both [[Test cricket|Test]] and [[One Day International]] level.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Players/255/255691/Under-19_Test_Matches.html Under-19 Test Matches played by Tim Armstrong (2)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref><ref>[http://cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Players/255/255691/Under-19_ODI_Matches.html Under-19 ODI Matches played by Tim Armstrong (13)] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> This included the [[2010 ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup]], during which Armstrong scored 240 runs to lead Australia's tournament [[batting average]]s.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Events/12/ICC_Under-19_World_Cup_2009-10/Australia_Under-19s_Batting.html Batting and Fielding for Australia Under-19s] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> Having played several matches as an [[all-rounder]] for the New South Wales under-23 side in the [[Futures League]], Armstrong was selected in New South Wales' squad for the [[2010<U+2013>11 KFC Twenty20 Big Bash]] tournament,<ref>''"Debutant Tim Armstrong, 20, has been named in the NSW squad after impressing in the Futures League Twenty20 carnival in Melbourne..."'' Braid, Marcus (2011). [http://www.smh.com.au/sport/cricket/callum-loses-fitness-race-to-face-blues-in-opener-20110103-19dvh.html Callum loses fitness race to face Blues in opener] <U+2013> ''[[Sydney Morning Herald]]''. Published 4 January 2011. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> and played a single match in the tournament, against [[Victoria cricket team|Victoria]] at the [[Melbourne Cricket Ground]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Scorecards/302/302045.html Victoria v New South Wales], KFC Twenty20 Big Bash 2010/11 <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> 

For the [[2011<U+2013>12 Big Bash League|inaugural season]] of the Big Bash League, Armstrong was signed by [[Sydney Thunder]]. He played three matches for the team, with a top score of 25 runs against Perth at [[ANZ Stadium]].<ref>[http://cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Players/255/255691/Twenty20_Matches.html Twenty20 Matches played by Tim Armstrong (4)] <U+2013><U+00A0>CricketArchive. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> Although remaining with the Thunder, Armstrong moved to [[Western Australia]] midway through the 2011<U+2013>12 Australian cricket season in an attempt to play regularly at state level. He debuted for the state in the [[2011<U+2013>12 Ryobi One-Day Cup]], in a match against New South Wales at the [[WACA Ground]], which remains his only match at [[List A cricket|List A]] level. Batting at number six, Armstrong was dismissed for a [[Duck (cricket)|golden duck]] whilst batting, but took the wicket of [[Ben Rohrer]] in New South Wales' innings, and finished with 1/15 from six overs.<ref>[http://cricketarchive.co.uk/Archive/Scorecards/348/348956.html Western Australia v New South Wales] <U+2013> CricketArchive. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> Although not offered a state contract by the [[Western Australian Cricket Association]], Armstrong was signed by the Perth Scorchers in July 2012.<ref>''"Perth expanded its squad to 15 with the announcement of former Sydney Thunder all-rounder Tim Armstrong..."'' [http://www.perthnow.com.au/sport/cricket/nathan-coulter-nile-and-ben-edmondson-re-sign-with-perth-scorchers-for-t20-big-bash/story-e6frg26c-1226427267638 Nathan Coulter-Nile and Ben Edmondson re-sign with Perth Scorchers for T20 Big Bash] <U+2013> PerthNow. Published 16 July 2012. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref> At [[Western Australian Grade Cricket|grade cricket]] level, Armstrong plays for the [[Fremantle District Cricket Club]].<ref>[http://www.waca.com.au/other/news_detail.php?ID=2650 WACA District First Grade: Round 3 Preview] <U+2013> Western Australian Cricket Association. Published 3 November 2012. Retrieved 14 November 2012.</ref>

